<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1157,454,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,282,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be characterised by the following features: Body length 
<quantity box="[160,330,490,515]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.4">1.40–1.80 mm</quantity>
. Head and mesosoma shiny black. Lateral and inferior area of face striated; in frontal view with strong dorso-ventral ridge adjacent to torulus. Female antenna with last seven or eight flagellomeres with rhinaria. Occiput smooth. Pronotal plate slightly striated. Inferior part of pronotum side slightly striated. Dorsal surface of scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[536,659,628,653]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1399,1422]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-11@5.[163,1153,142,1382]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Hydrelliaeucoila egeria Díaz and Gallardo. A. Antenna of female. B. Head in frontal view. C. Antenna of female. D. Pronotal plate. E. Scutellum and propodeum. F. Mesosoma in lateral view. G. Base of metasoma. (Modified from Díaz et al. 2009.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758281/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Figure 1b</figureCitation>
) coarsely sculptured, reticulate-rugose. Scutellar foveae (
<figureCitation box="[374,491,663,688]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1399,1422]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-11@5.[163,1153,142,1382]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Hydrelliaeucoila egeria Díaz and Gallardo. A. Antenna of female. B. Head in frontal view. C. Antenna of female. D. Pronotal plate. E. Scutellum and propodeum. F. Mesosoma in lateral view. G. Base of metasoma. (Modified from Díaz et al. 2009.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758281/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Figure 1b</figureCitation>
) at base slightly sculptured, oval, shorter than wide. Lateral bars of scutellum with foveae beneath. Scutellar plate (
<figureCitation box="[933,1045,698,723]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1399,1422]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-11@5.[163,1153,142,1382]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 1. Hydrelliaeucoila egeria Díaz and Gallardo. A. Antenna of female. B. Head in frontal view. C. Antenna of female. D. Pronotal plate. E. Scutellum and propodeum. F. Mesosoma in lateral view. G. Base of metasoma. (Modified from Díaz et al. 2009.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758281/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Figure 1c</figureCitation>
) without a dark impression on the entire edge. Middle and ventral part of mesopleuron, above mesopleural carina with few striations. Metapleuron slightly sculptured. Marginal cell of fore wing partially open (
<bibRefCitation author="Diaz NB &amp; Gallardo FE &amp; Gaddi AL &amp; Cabrera Walsh G" box="[495,681,802,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" pagination="603 - 607" refId="ref4593" refString="Diaz NB, Gallardo FE, Gaddi AL, Cabrera Walsh G. 2009. Description of a new genus and species of Eucoilinae (Hymenoptera: Cynipoidea: Figitidae) parasitoid of ephydridae (Diptera). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 104 (4): 603 - 607." type="journal article" year="2009">Díaz et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[160,524,870,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,524,870,896]" box="[160,524,870,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,301,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Description.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Diaz NB &amp; Gallardo FE &amp; Gaddi AL &amp; Cabrera Walsh G" box="[345,518,871,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" pagination="603 - 607" refId="ref4593" refString="Diaz NB, Gallardo FE, Gaddi AL, Cabrera Walsh G. 2009. Description of a new genus and species of Eucoilinae (Hymenoptera: Cynipoidea: Figitidae) parasitoid of ephydridae (Diptera). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 104 (4): 603 - 607." type="journal article" year="2009">Díaz et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,940,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,254,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Biology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Diaz and Gallardo" authorityName="Diaz and Gallardo" box="[271,728,941,966]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeria">
<emphasis box="[271,522,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Hydrelliaeucoila egeria</emphasis>
Díaz and Gallardo
</taxonomicName>
parasitises pupae of 
<taxonomicName box="[966,1149,941,966]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Hydrellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeriae">
<emphasis box="[966,1149,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Hydrellia egeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These pupae are found fixed to the stems of 
<emphasis box="[673,763,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">E. densa</emphasis>
at the leaf axils of the last leaf the fly larva fed on. The gravid female parasitoid lays an egg in the host pupa, and continues exploring the stem for more pupae. During the warm season, the parasitoid takes around one month to develop. Parasitoids that have not emerged by the end of fall diapause as larvae in the host puparium until the following spring. Laboratory observations reveal that the female parasitoid sometimes explores branches devoid of fly pupae, so apparently it selects 
<emphasis box="[520,611,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">E. densa</emphasis>
branches at random, and not by detecting the presence of the host fly (
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera Walsh G &amp; Mattioli F" box="[444,821,1218,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refId="ref4551" refString="Cabrera Walsh G, Mattioli F. 2007. Brazillian waterweed. http: // www. usda-sabcl. org." type="url" year="2007">Cabrera Walsh and Mattioli 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera Walsh G &amp; Mattioli F" box="[834,890,1218,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refId="ref4572" refString="Cabrera Walsh G, Mattioli F. 2008. Brazillian waterweed. http: // www. usda-sabcl. org." type="url" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Diaz NB &amp; Gallardo FE &amp; Gaddi AL &amp; Cabrera Walsh G" box="[903,1079,1218,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" pagination="603 - 607" refId="ref4593" refString="Diaz NB, Gallardo FE, Gaddi AL, Cabrera Walsh G. 2009. Description of a new genus and species of Eucoilinae (Hymenoptera: Cynipoidea: Figitidae) parasitoid of ephydridae (Diptera). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 104 (4): 603 - 607." type="journal article" year="2009">Díaz et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1286,1416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,307,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Distribution.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[330,425,1287,1312]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1096,1119]" captionTargetBox="[165,1152,143,1078]" captionTargetId="figure-100@8.[163,1153,142,1079]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of Hydrelliaeucoila species from Argentina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758289" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758289/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[447,560,1287,1312]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. Recorded from Otamendi (
<bibRefCitation author="Diaz NB &amp; Gallardo FE &amp; Gaddi AL &amp; Cabrera Walsh G" box="[880,1060,1287,1312]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" pagination="603 - 607" refId="ref4593" refString="Diaz NB, Gallardo FE, Gaddi AL, Cabrera Walsh G. 2009. Description of a new genus and species of Eucoilinae (Hymenoptera: Cynipoidea: Figitidae) parasitoid of ephydridae (Diptera). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 104 (4): 603 - 607." type="journal article" year="2009">Diaz et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and La Plata (new record), 
<collectingRegion box="[374,622,1322,1347]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
and Yacutinga (new record), 
<collectingRegion box="[948,1152,1322,1347]" country="Argentina" name="Misiones" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Misiones province</collectingRegion>
. This distribution belongs to the Pampean province for 
<collectingRegion box="[768,911,1357,1382]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
and Parana Forest for 
<collectingRegion box="[160,258,1391,1416]" country="Argentina" name="Misiones" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Misiones</collectingRegion>
(Chacoan subregion).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="231" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1460,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,296,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[312,573,1461,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="egeria">
<emphasis box="[312,573,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Hydrelliaeucoila egeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other two species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[160,271,1495,1520]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Argentina</collectingCountry>
by presenting the following combination of characters: head and mesosoma black (reddish brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[434,508,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[434,508,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. rufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[515,605,1530,1555]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; dark brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[780,921,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[780,921,1530,1555]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[929,1019,1530,1555]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); lateral and inferior area of face striated (smooth in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[600,673,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[600,673,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. rufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[679,766,1565,1590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[820,960,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[820,960,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[967,1056,1565,1590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); head in frontal view with ridge adjacent to torulus (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[793,937,1599,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata">
<emphasis box="[793,937,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); medial bridge of pronotal plate broad (narrow in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[520,592,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[520,592,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. rufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[599,685,1634,1659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[740,880,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nonstriata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[740,880,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. nonstriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[887,976,1634,1659]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); without a dark impression on the entire edge of scutellar plate (with a dark impression on the entire edge in 
<taxonomicName authority="Reche &amp; Gallardo, 2022" authorityName="Reche &amp; Gallardo" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,262,1703,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Hydrelliaeucoila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,262,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">H. rufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[270,360,1703,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
